Service Manager Proxy exposes
GetServiceEnvironment and
ListServiceEnvironments only in the pinned SDK,
so the published runtime is bind-existing and
observe-only.
Bind identity is explicit: reconcile requires
compartmentId and serviceEnvironmentId, tracks
the returned Service Manager identifier in
status, and uses ListServiceEnvironments only to
confirm absence after a reread no longer finds
the tracked environment.
No OCI create, update, or delete operation is
published. The controller treats
serviceEnvironmentId and compartmentId as
bind-only identity and performs Kubernetes-local
finalizer cleanup on delete.
Entitlement transitions beginning with BEGIN_
requeue, stable entitlement states settle
success, and FAILED_* plus TRA_UNKNOWN remain
terminal failures.
end note
